WEBVTT

00:00.802 --> 00:14.480
So last night we tried to argue that saving faith is the awakening, the coming to life of the enjoyment of Jesus.

00:17.163 --> 00:28.338
And if that's true, then since saving faith is a obligation for all human beings, therefore

00:28.450 --> 00:32.735
the enjoyment of Jesus would be an obligation, a duty, a requirement.

00:34.497 --> 00:44.550
A lot of people stumble over that claim that to enjoy Jesus is required of us.

00:46.652 --> 00:47.553
It's an obligation.

00:47.714 --> 00:52.600
So I'm posing the question in this message, is that a biblical way to think?

00:53.901 --> 00:57.746
Should you even think about, okay, when I get up tomorrow morning,

00:59.458 --> 01:05.063
One of the things God requires of me is that I enjoy Him that day.

01:05.564 --> 01:12.210
It is a requirement that feels very strange to a lot of people.

01:13.151 --> 01:16.174
So that's my question this evening.

01:17.415 --> 01:28.306
And I invite you to turn with me to Psalm 1611, a well-known text around here, right at the heart of what we do at Desiring God and Bethlehem College in seminary.

01:32.738 --> 01:59.314
So let me read just this one verse on our way to give six reasons for why it is biblical to make the pursuit of the enjoyment of God, the vocation of your life, the calling and obligation, a very high priority, not something peripheral, but something essential.

02:02.178 --> 02:10.250
You, God, this is verse 11, Psalm 16, you make known to me the path of life.

02:12.813 --> 02:19.843
In your presence, there is fullness of joy, and in your right hand are pleasures forevermore.

02:21.325 --> 02:30.258
So Father, as we look at this verse and then broaden out our sight to the rest of the Bible, would you come and get glory

02:30.498 --> 02:44.137
While we get to joy and I pray that in this room, those who find it foreign or alien to their life, that the enjoyment of Jesus would be paramount, would be saved.

02:46.520 --> 02:54.011
That you would bring saving faith into their lives and thus awaken the enjoyment of Jesus.

02:56.294 --> 02:58.157
I ask for this miracle in Jesus' name.

02:58.898 --> 02:59.218
Amen.

02:59.874 --> 03:03.520
So seven brief observations about this verse.

03:04.101 --> 03:09.229
Number one, there is a path that leads to the presence of God.

03:11.132 --> 03:13.275
You may know to me the path of life.

03:13.295 --> 03:14.637
There's a path of life.

03:14.998 --> 03:16.800
Get on it, right?

03:16.820 --> 03:17.361
Are you on it?

03:17.902 --> 03:23.851
That would be the question that the Holy Spirit would be pressing on you if you were meditating on this verse.

03:23.871 --> 03:24.753
Am I on that path?

03:24.793 --> 03:28.178
Number two, God is the one who makes the path known.

03:28.706 --> 03:32.149
You make known to me the path of life.

03:32.169 --> 03:33.250
So He directs us to it.

03:33.951 --> 03:34.812
He puts us on it.

03:35.373 --> 03:47.524
Number three, that path leads to fullness of joy, not 99% proof joy, but 100% proof joy.

03:48.185 --> 03:54.811
If the world offers me 98% joy and God offers me 100%, I'm not taking the world.

03:55.832 --> 03:57.394
That would be stupid, right?

03:57.794 --> 04:01.199
Most people are stupid.

04:01.219 --> 04:02.201
I mean, it's really insane.

04:02.221 --> 04:04.985
It's suicidal and it's insane.

04:06.267 --> 04:12.336
If God offers you full joy for you to take anything less is self-destructive.

04:13.598 --> 04:20.388
Fourth, this path leads to joy forever.

04:21.270 --> 04:24.114
So not just full, but

04:24.482 --> 04:25.163
forever.

04:25.223 --> 04:28.428
So I'm not interested in the offer of 80 years of joy.

04:28.448 --> 04:35.858
And then hell, I'm not interested in the offer of 80 million years of joy.

04:36.239 --> 04:36.900
No, thank you.

04:37.541 --> 04:44.230
I want joy forever, which is why I love to, I love to commend Christianity.

04:44.531 --> 04:47.275
I love to preach and say, come on, be a Christian.

04:47.555 --> 04:49.618
You cannot improve upon this offer.

04:50.050 --> 04:51.612
There's nothing fuller than full.

04:51.892 --> 04:53.594
There's nothing longer than forever.

04:53.934 --> 04:55.997
Why would you not come?

04:58.439 --> 05:06.328
Number five, this promise to have full and forever joy is in Christ.

05:07.189 --> 05:09.151
Now, that's not in the verse.

05:09.171 --> 05:11.214
However, we're Christians.

05:12.235 --> 05:15.218
What we know is that as the Old Testament,

05:15.682 --> 05:17.805
redemptive history unfolds.

05:18.286 --> 05:27.441
It comes to its fullness in Jesus as he comes into the world and is the Messiah and thus the fulfillment of the Old Testament.

05:27.661 --> 05:28.883
So you read a verse like this.

05:28.903 --> 05:34.993
2 Corinthians 1, 20, all the promises of God find their yes in Jesus.

05:36.195 --> 05:42.866
So this promise, 16, 11, in my presence, God says, is fullness of joy, pleasures forevermore,

05:42.978 --> 05:46.123
Jesus comes and purchases it for sinners.

05:46.143 --> 05:51.753
The only reason anybody could enjoy this in the Old Testament is because Jesus was going to shed his blood for sinners.

05:52.494 --> 05:58.945
So it's not artificial to say this verse was purchased for us by Jesus.

05:59.305 --> 06:02.130
So if you are in Christ tonight, it's yours.

06:02.722 --> 06:05.965
You don't have to say, oh, but that was made as a promise to Israel.

06:05.986 --> 06:07.908
It's not made to Gentiles like me.

06:07.948 --> 06:10.510
Yes, it is because you are in the Messiah.

06:10.931 --> 06:16.617
He is the Jew and now everything promised to Israel is yours in Messiah Jesus.

06:17.097 --> 06:22.623
Number six, the full and lasting joy is in God's presence.

06:22.643 --> 06:23.865
It's nowhere else to be found.

06:24.185 --> 06:32.434
He is not holding this out as one of many options like, oh, you can find full and lasting joy in my presence and you can find full and lasting joy elsewhere.

06:32.706 --> 06:34.529
That's not what the verse means.

06:34.969 --> 06:47.648
The verse means if you're gonna have full joy and forever joy, it will be from God, in God's presence, and therefore, number seven, it's an obligation, as we're going.

06:47.668 --> 06:48.409
It's an obligation.

06:49.691 --> 06:54.559
He's not pointing you to this path to say, you don't have to do this.

06:55.400 --> 06:57.062
And there are other ways to life.

06:57.924 --> 06:59.426
There are other paths to life.

06:59.666 --> 07:00.127
There aren't.

07:00.708 --> 07:02.290
There's one path to life.

07:02.402 --> 07:10.172
One path to joy, one path to God, and Jesus is saying, God is saying, get on it.

07:11.174 --> 07:11.815
Get on it.

07:12.095 --> 07:15.920
It's one of the happiest obligations you will ever have.

07:15.960 --> 07:19.405
I mean, it is the happiest obligation you will ever have.

07:19.985 --> 07:21.828
It's a duty, it's a requirement.

07:22.128 --> 07:28.597
Get on the path that leads to your full and forever joy.

07:29.118 --> 07:29.458
Now,

07:31.106 --> 07:46.850
It might be gratuitous to ask, why have I given the last 55 years of my life to thinking about that reality, that obligation and written book after book about it and grow up a school and a ministry around it?

07:46.910 --> 07:49.734
Why have you given yourself to this?

07:49.774 --> 08:00.530
I mean, couldn't it be that this thing that you call enjoying Jesus or Christian hedonism is

08:00.834 --> 08:14.371
just a warmed-over form of prosperity gospel, kind of prosperity light, that horrible stuff that we have exported around the world by American Christianity.

08:15.532 --> 08:16.473
Maybe it's just that.

08:17.755 --> 08:27.026
Or maybe it's just a disguised form of pop psychology fitting right in with the American meism

08:27.714 --> 08:38.969
And of course, people are going to like to hear this because we're all into ourselves and Piper's going around the country saying, indulge yourself on full and forever joy.

08:39.029 --> 08:41.893
How easy does that fit into sin?

08:45.498 --> 08:51.166
Or maybe it's just true, but it's marginal and Piper treats it as central.

08:53.369 --> 08:57.234
Now, I don't think any of those three is true or I wouldn't be here.

08:58.370 --> 09:02.878
So let me give you four reasons before I even give you my six reasons.

09:06.184 --> 09:07.826
Six reasons for why it's an obligation.

09:07.846 --> 09:09.509
And four reasons why I care.

09:10.211 --> 09:12.114
Like why did we accept this invitation?

09:12.154 --> 09:13.276
We got things to do, right?

09:13.516 --> 09:14.037
I'm old.

09:15.199 --> 09:18.946
I'm trying to finish some projects and I keep interrupting them to do things like this.

09:19.046 --> 09:21.490
Why did I do this?

09:24.770 --> 09:27.754
And I have four reasons and they're a big deal.

09:27.834 --> 09:29.496
You will see that very quickly.

09:29.516 --> 09:45.136
Number one, it has this, enjoying Jesus, this church with that tagline, enjoying Jesus, the pursuit, the obligation of full and forever joy in God's presence has everything to do with suffering.

09:46.878 --> 09:48.821
And every person in this room will suffer.

09:49.301 --> 09:50.823
No exceptions.

09:50.843 --> 09:53.106
I know that not because of life,

09:53.218 --> 09:55.642
enough to teach me, but because of the Bible.

09:56.764 --> 10:01.793
Through many tribulations, we must enter the kingdom of God, Acts 14, 22.

10:01.873 --> 10:06.501
Whoever would live a godly life in Christ Jesus will be persecuted.

10:06.521 --> 10:08.464
2 Timothy 3, 12.

10:08.804 --> 10:15.095
If anyone would come after me, let him deny himself and take up his cross, which is the place to suffer and die.

10:15.456 --> 10:16.818
Matthew 16.

10:16.898 --> 10:23.046
We are fellow heirs with Christ, provided we suffer with Him in order that we may be glorified with Him.

10:23.307 --> 10:25.430
You're going to suffer, Christian.

10:25.470 --> 10:32.259
This issue of enjoying Jesus has everything to do with doing that well.

10:34.662 --> 10:37.246
If you don't get this, you won't suffer well.

10:38.387 --> 10:39.088
That's number one.

10:39.669 --> 10:46.098
I care about your suffering and therefore I care about making plain what enjoyment

10:46.178 --> 10:48.742
of Jesus is and isn't.

10:49.362 --> 10:50.925
Number two, why do I care?

10:51.986 --> 10:56.092
It has everything to do with loving other people.

10:57.654 --> 11:01.199
The Bible says, if you love your neighbor, you have fulfilled the whole law.

11:01.479 --> 11:02.581
That's a big deal, right?

11:03.061 --> 11:03.702
That's huge.

11:04.003 --> 11:05.665
You can fulfill the whole law.

11:05.685 --> 11:06.125
How?

11:06.606 --> 11:07.848
By loving people.

11:07.888 --> 11:12.574
Love your neighbor as yourself has, you have fulfilled the whole law, Romans 13, 10.

11:14.617 --> 11:15.218
How is that?

11:15.586 --> 11:16.827
Well, what's more loving?

11:18.088 --> 11:28.058
I mean, can anything be more loving than to lay down your life in order to bring other people into full and forever joy.

11:28.378 --> 11:36.205
There isn't any greater love than to bring people into full and forever joy at the cost of your life.

11:37.066 --> 11:39.328
You can't give what you don't have.

11:39.388 --> 11:43.953
It's a fake.

11:43.973 --> 11:45.234
You're just a fake.

11:45.442 --> 11:54.016
If you think you're giving what you don't have, and therefore if you are indifferent to enjoying Jesus, you can't love people.

11:55.498 --> 11:57.661
Now I'm coming back to that, so I'll leave it right there.

11:58.042 --> 11:59.244
That's a big deal to me.

12:00.065 --> 12:02.970
I would like this church to love people better.

12:02.990 --> 12:05.594
I would like to love people better.

12:05.954 --> 12:09.220
You can't love people better if you don't enjoy Jesus.

12:10.081 --> 12:10.802
Number three.

12:14.178 --> 12:16.261
It has everything to do with the glory of God.

12:16.321 --> 12:22.049
The glory of God is the greatest reality in the universe.

12:22.229 --> 12:24.873
God is the greatest reality in the universe.

12:24.933 --> 12:38.012
His glory is the outshining of himself and it is impossible that you make God glorious if you desire other things more than God.

12:38.793 --> 12:39.634
You cannot do it.

12:43.746 --> 12:47.692
and therefore the enjoyment of Jesus is essential to glorifying God.

12:47.712 --> 12:49.595
We'll come back to that one as well.

12:50.036 --> 12:51.598
You see how massive this is for me?

12:52.760 --> 12:58.589
Suffering, love, God, glory, it's just huge.

12:59.030 --> 13:01.834
We're not talking about marginal things in this conference.

13:02.275 --> 13:04.519
This church is not about marginal things.

13:04.759 --> 13:07.163
Like let's have a cute little tagline.

13:07.984 --> 13:10.128
What would work in Middle-Othean?

13:10.949 --> 13:11.730
Well, maybe

13:11.810 --> 13:12.771
enjoying Jesus.

13:12.792 --> 13:14.093
That's just a lot of baloney.

13:15.115 --> 13:19.522
This is as deep and as central, as glorious as it gets.

13:20.523 --> 13:21.104
That's why I'm here.

13:21.805 --> 13:23.728
I don't like marginal stuff.

13:25.391 --> 13:31.861
Number four, it has everything to do with your identity as a human being.

13:33.663 --> 13:37.970
Now this has come to the front for me because of artificial intelligence.

13:40.098 --> 13:47.432
If you say five years ago were asked, what's right at the core of being in the image of God?

13:48.334 --> 13:52.883
If you had said, it's the capacity to reason.

13:54.386 --> 13:57.151
Almost everybody was, yeah, that's an important part of it.

13:57.451 --> 13:59.155
The capacity to reason.

13:59.716 --> 14:02.962
God is a rational being.

14:03.362 --> 14:06.566
And he has made us in his image and we are rational beings.

14:06.606 --> 14:11.593
And then you wake up one morning and machines can think better than you and talk better than you.

14:11.833 --> 14:12.514
And they can.

14:12.554 --> 14:14.356
They can.

14:14.416 --> 14:18.922
They can outthink you and out speak you.

14:20.704 --> 14:22.326
Now what becomes of your humanity?

14:26.371 --> 14:28.434
That's not the essence of who you are.

14:30.370 --> 14:38.880
The essence of who you are is the spiritual capacity of your soul to see and savor the glory of Jesus.

14:40.822 --> 14:50.073
No machine will ever see and savor, enjoy, be passionate about Jesus.

14:50.313 --> 14:51.154
It won't ever happen.

14:52.095 --> 14:54.738
It will think, it will not feel.

14:54.758 --> 14:58.322
It will say, I feel,

14:58.594 --> 15:00.556
program it to say anything.

15:01.878 --> 15:02.599
It won't feel.

15:02.619 --> 15:17.816
I mean, this has just been huge for me recently as I've seen how what we've given our lives to for the last 50 years is so pointedly relevant and so essential for the very nature of human being.

15:17.836 --> 15:23.803
Okay, so no, it's not prosperity gospel.

15:23.944 --> 15:26.066
No, it's not a bit of pop psychology.

15:28.226 --> 15:30.370
It's everything.

15:30.390 --> 15:31.592
It's my life.

15:31.992 --> 15:32.854
It's your life.

15:33.776 --> 15:35.398
Okay, now we go to the six reasons.

15:36.360 --> 15:47.700
The six reasons for why your pursuit of the enjoyment of Jesus full and forever is an obligation.

15:49.843 --> 15:53.810
A very, very happy obligation.

15:57.890 --> 16:01.193
Number one, it's commanded.

16:02.495 --> 16:04.917
It's commanded in the Bible.

16:06.138 --> 16:08.881
You heard this if you were in Marshall's seminar today.

16:10.903 --> 16:15.728
Psalm 37, four, delight yourself in the Lord is not a suggestion.

16:17.149 --> 16:17.730
It's a command.

16:18.951 --> 16:23.756
Psalm 32, verse one, be glad in the Lord and rejoice you righteous ones.

16:24.176 --> 16:26.258
Shout for joy, all you are

16:26.498 --> 16:28.260
who are upright in heart, that's a command.

16:29.322 --> 16:39.355
Psalm 67 verse four, let the nations be glad and sing for joy, for you will judge the peoples with uprightness and guide the nations on the earth.

16:39.415 --> 16:44.381
Isn't it wonderful that world missions means going to tell the nations to be happy?

16:45.503 --> 16:46.624
That's just wonderful.

16:46.684 --> 16:47.786
It may cost you your life.

16:47.806 --> 16:51.130
I mean, I do funerals for missionaries.

16:52.152 --> 16:54.034
I know this will cost you your life.

16:54.114 --> 16:57.920
I promise my people there will be martyrs in this church.

16:58.701 --> 17:00.264
Come on, let's do this.

17:01.445 --> 17:03.949
The Great Commission won't be finished without blood.

17:03.969 --> 17:05.332
It says so in Revelation.

17:06.313 --> 17:11.040
The martyrs are up there waiting and Jesus says, the full number of the martyrs isn't in yet.

17:11.061 --> 17:12.122
It can't end history.

17:12.984 --> 17:14.185
It's a serious business.

17:14.386 --> 17:17.491
But what we're doing is saying, let the nations be glad.

17:18.632 --> 17:22.258
We're telling the best news in the world, Psalm 100.

17:22.562 --> 17:25.185
Make a joyful noise to the Lord, all the earth.

17:25.906 --> 17:27.929
Serve the Lord with gladness.

17:28.209 --> 17:29.230
It's a command.

17:29.250 --> 17:32.014
Now, that's argument number one.

17:32.054 --> 17:32.755
It's a command.

17:33.556 --> 17:36.780
And there are two objections, two objections to it.

17:38.642 --> 17:42.066
And these objections are right under my history.

17:42.547 --> 17:48.434
The first objection is, I was on a panel with Elizabeth Elliot.

17:48.578 --> 17:51.763
Elizabeth Elliott was, was, is one of my heroes.

17:52.264 --> 17:52.785
I liked her.

17:52.865 --> 17:54.247
I liked just by everything about her.

17:54.287 --> 17:55.228
She was blunt.

17:55.569 --> 17:56.630
She was straightforward.

17:57.091 --> 17:58.533
She was in your face.

17:58.994 --> 18:00.777
I just thought she was the coolest lady.

18:03.261 --> 18:05.664
And now Johnny Eriksantata has kind of taken her place.

18:06.105 --> 18:11.473
So I get these two women in my life that, besides my wife, that are just awesomely inspiring to me.

18:12.555 --> 18:13.056
Okay, women.

18:14.218 --> 18:14.959
Here's what she said.

18:15.319 --> 18:17.042
Gotta have to correct Elizabeth Elliott.

18:17.826 --> 18:19.669
So I'm on this panel with her.

18:20.049 --> 18:21.351
She's 20 years older than I am.

18:21.812 --> 18:24.295
I checked that out this afternoon, born in 26.

18:24.335 --> 18:28.001
She's in heaven with Jesus.

18:28.602 --> 18:29.904
Got this all straightened out now.

18:35.051 --> 18:37.094
And she said flat out in front of 2,000 people.

18:39.137 --> 18:42.181
John, I don't think you should tell people to pursue joy.

18:42.201 --> 18:45.426
I think you should tell people to pursue obedience.

18:49.090 --> 18:54.335
And I've heard this before, so this is not catching me off guard, right?

18:54.355 --> 19:06.086
And I said, I didn't call, I probably did not call her Elizabeth because I was in my 40s probably and she was in her 60s and I don't call women in their 60s by their first name.

19:06.366 --> 19:07.628
When I'm 40, I do now.

19:13.894 --> 19:18.578
I said, that's like saying don't tell

19:18.658 --> 19:22.844
people to eat apples, tell them to eat fruit.

19:26.810 --> 19:27.271
You get that?

19:28.833 --> 19:32.979
Because obedience means doing what you're told.

19:33.039 --> 19:36.905
And what we're told is to be glad in God.

19:38.988 --> 19:39.308
Right?

19:39.989 --> 19:40.951
It's a command.

19:40.991 --> 19:46.259
You can't play obedience off of an obedient act.

19:46.900 --> 19:48.562
It will work.

19:49.410 --> 19:50.812
I think I won that argument.

19:54.036 --> 19:56.579
I wouldn't change anything about her.

19:56.619 --> 19:59.143
She's going around the country telling people to die for Jesus.

19:59.863 --> 20:02.307
That's the name of her biography of Amy Carmichael, right?

20:02.367 --> 20:03.608
Anybody know the name of her biography?

20:04.249 --> 20:05.270
A chance to die.

20:06.672 --> 20:07.353
I love this.

20:07.794 --> 20:14.863
So I'm not asking her to change her language, but I'm telling her, you can't make me change mine either because it's biblical.

20:15.223 --> 20:17.426
You're just biblical, mine's biblical.

20:18.338 --> 20:20.100
That's objection number one.

20:20.581 --> 20:27.209
It is not fair to say to Piper, you should tell people to obey God instead of enjoy God.

20:28.791 --> 20:32.416
Because enjoying God is obedient to the command to enjoy God.

20:33.457 --> 20:46.674
Objection number two, here I am a sophomore, I'm a junior in college and I took a class on apologetics from Millard Erickson.

20:46.786 --> 20:54.834
He had us read a bad book, and he knew it was a bad book because that's how he did apologetics, named Situation Ethics by Joseph Fletcher.

20:55.635 --> 21:05.485
And in the book, now here's one of the great advantages of growing up in a church and in a home where it's all Bible saturated because you develop a good sniffer, right?

21:06.006 --> 21:08.529
You can't explain what's wrong, but you smell it.

21:08.689 --> 21:09.229
It's wrong.

21:09.370 --> 21:10.150
Something's wrong.

21:11.472 --> 21:13.714
And so I'm reading this book, and here's the argument.

21:16.226 --> 21:28.324
Love for people cannot involve the emotions because it's commanded, and you can't command the emotions.

21:28.344 --> 21:32.190
Some's wrong with that.

21:33.471 --> 21:37.217
I've never heard anybody argue like that, but I said, that doesn't smell right to me.

21:37.237 --> 21:39.560
Now you know why that doesn't smell right to me?

21:40.482 --> 21:43.346
Because emotions are commanded all over the Bible.

21:44.866 --> 22:13.106
Come on Joseph Fletcher read the Bible and you I just want to pause here and say All you people who don't have PhDs in theology You've got noses and if you if you grew up with the aroma of the gospel and the aroma of an inspired Bible You're going to be guided by that good sniffer all through life and all these liberal PhDs are going to try to tell you things like

22:13.986 --> 22:16.350
That doesn't work in the Bible.

22:16.410 --> 22:18.513
That's just wonderful.

22:19.014 --> 22:23.882
So just keep reading your Bibles and you'll be on the path.

22:23.902 --> 22:25.285
So what's the answer to that?

22:25.745 --> 22:28.490
The answer is, desires are commanded.

22:28.510 --> 22:33.879
1 Peter 2, 2, like newborn babes desire the pure spiritual milk.

22:33.899 --> 22:35.401
Contentment is commanded.

22:35.441 --> 22:38.386
Hebrews

22:38.754 --> 22:40.617
13, be content with what you have.

22:41.058 --> 22:42.119
Hope is commanded.

22:42.159 --> 22:43.201
Hope in God.

22:43.401 --> 22:45.645
Psalm 42, fear is commanded.

